name: Eleto Chocolate Cafe
directions: On the ground floor, towards the back, on the left hand side just past the steps leading upstairs. Through the door, follow some steps down and you’ll find them.
comment:
The cafe itself is accessible but the toilets are not.
As this is my first time visiting, I cannot currently gauge the tolerance towards just using the place for the toilet.

name: PEP Place/PEP Employment Centre
directions: There are 2 non gendered singled occupancy washrooms on the 3rd floor. There is a staircase that goes up to the 3rd floor, also an elevator. If taking the stairs, there will be a door. It is the entrance to Pep Place, which is a mental health drop in center. The elevator will take you directly into the center's hallway by the door to the entrance. The washooms are just down the hall from the entrance to the enter on the right past the kitchen and the laundry room. There are also non gender single room accessable washooms on the second floor, which is the Pep Employment Centre.
comment: The centre likes people who use their services to sign a membership form for statistics. This is not a requirement to use their washrooms.

name: UNCG Campus Ministry Building

comment: The bathrooms are gendered but you're safe to use whichever you prefer. Bathrooms available both upstairs and down, right next to the elevator. Interfaith building, Lutherans especially very accepting. It's the only restroom on campus I've felt safe using my preferred room.

Ingen kommer til å bry seg, men hvis du er nervøs kan du begynne å ta av deg jakken på vegen inn?

Nobody will care, but if you're nervous you can start taking off your jacket before you enter?
